                <span class="h2">MUSQOT ONLINE HELP</span>
            </p><p>
            <span class="h1">Explanation of how cost centers are used in Musqot<br/></span>
            </p><p>
            <span class="h3">Basic use of cost centers<br/></span>
            <span class="body">All organizations that use Musqot need to setup at least one cost center in the application. This cost center will be the source (sponsor) of all financial funds that are later to be requested from Plan owners.<br/></span>        
            </p><p>
            <span class="body">If your marketing organization does not wish to leverage all the benefits of advanced cost center usage, you need not bother spending any time on this. You can simply add a “place holder” cost center, name it whatever you like, save it (so that the application has a cost center entity to connect with funding requests etc) and not give it another thought.<br/></span>        
            </p><p>
            <span class="h3">Advanced use of Cost centers<br/></span>
            <span class="body">In large organizations however, marketing funds are often pitched in from many different sources. In order to keep track of the various internal stakeholders, and the funds they have most likely agreed to sponsor for specific purposes, it is a good idea to create a unique cost center for each such sponsor (for example a department, a subsidiary company, a partner organization, a product area who’s manager has granted you financial support, etc).<br/></span>     
            </p><p>
            <span class="body">The Owner of the cost center will receive funding requests from Plan owners who select the cost center as their financial source/sponsor.<br/></span>     
            </p><p>
            <span class="h3">Benefits<br/></span>
            <span class="body">Setting up cost centers in Musqot that represents your actual organizational structure, from a financial perspective, will help you to validate that each penny is being allocated to the purpose it was intended for. <br/></span> 
